Powered by RubiQube Ad Network UYO – Jungle justice was on Wednesday averted in Eket, Akwa Ibom State when the Police rescued a youth burglar from being lynched by irate youths. It has become a practice in this part of the country that once caught stealing by the youths, the individual faces jungle justice by being burnt alive. Sources told Daily Independent that the suspect, was caught resting at the crime scene by the shop owner after breaking the ceilings of a lock up store in a boutique located at no. 18 Uqua road Eket. A witness, Mr Solomon Akpan said the 18 –year-old man from Ikot Ekpene was caught right inside the shop after he had arranged all clothes but could not escaped through the ceiling which he used in gaining access to the boutique at night. Solomon said the owner of the shop Affiong arrived in the morning and saw the tired thief on the floor with the looted wares as he could not escape. When contacted, Affiong said she was afraid when she opened her shop and saw someone sitting on the floor with heaps of clothes carefully arranged beside him. “I was afraid to see an unknown person inside my shop as I open it for business of the day. I raised the alarm which attracted neighbours who arrested him.” The landlord of the shop Mr Tommy Edoho said the burglar was beaten to a pulp before he was taken to the youth’s president of Ekpene Ukpa village Mr Ime also known as ‘Presido’ for interrogation. Our correspondent gathered that some angry youths intercepted the protesters at Ekpene Ukpa junction near Later Glory Church where the suspect was forced to sit on the tarred road and was given some ‘blows’ from the mob. Chanting war songs such as “ thief oooo”, “ino”, kill him” the protesters ordered for petrol to burn the suspect alive. It was gathered that the youth president Mr Ime who could not contain the mob immediately called the police Anti – Cultism unit , Eket Division who arrived at the scene of the incident and rescued the victim from the mob action.